The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, May 29, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Mumbai, May 28: The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) today announced the amended disclosure and investor protection guidelines that will restrict the practice of splitting shares before initial public offers (IPOs). The guidelines, which could impact future public issues, provide a definition of the minimum application value. The regulator also decided to introduce proportionate allotment within the specified categories and reservation for retail investors.																								 New Delhi, May 28: The rate of inflation rose 0.47 per cent to 4.67 per cent for the week ended May 15 due to surging prices of mass consumption items like vegetables, milk and edible oils. The point-to-point wholesale price index inflation stood at 4.20 per cent in the previous week.																								 New Delhi, May 28: Finance minister P. Chidambaram today cleared 24 foreign direct investment (FDI) proposals worth Rs 37.86 crore. 																								 Mumbai, May 28: The Reserve Bank plans to advise banks to formulate a transparent and comprehensive policy defining the rights of depositors in general, and small depositors in particular, by July 31.																								 Turin, May 28: Fiat chairman Umberto Agnelli died of cancer on Thursday, ending an era at Italys largest industrial group.
